result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Larry M Urick in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Defendant Larry M Urick in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 13CF51, 13CF163, 14CF55, 14CF132, 14CF135, 14CF141 @ 9:50 a.m. Written proposed resolution filed. 13CF51 SAR, Recommending ct 1 - time served, 90 days, ct 2 - 180 days jail, concurrent, credit for 135 days, ct 3 - 180 days jail, concurrent, credit for 135 days. Civil judgment for court costs. Atty Laufenberg and Def agree. Def has nothing to say. Court accepts agreement. Ct 1 - 90 days jail, credit for time served. Ct 2 - 180 days concurrent, 135 days credit. Ct 3 - 180 days concurrent, 135 days credit. Civil judgment for court costs. State has complied with victim notification requirements on all cases. 13CF163 - Deferred judgment revoked, withheld sentence, 18 months probation, costs. Atty Laufenberg and Def agree. Nothing by Def.  Court accepts agreement. Deferred judgment revoked, sentence withheld, 18 months probation, costs. 14CF55 - State amends ct 1 to misd bail jumping 946.49(1)(a), ct 2 dismiss read in, withheld sentence 1 yr probation, concurrent, costs. (Review of overall agreement by Court and Counsel) Court reviews Def's understanding of proceedings. 14CF55 plea to amended ct 1 - no contest. 14CF135 ct 1 - no contest plea, ct 3 - no contest plea. 14CF141 ct 1 - no contest plea, ct 2 amended to misd bail jumping as repeater - no contest. 14CF135 - Court reviews repeater penalties. Def still pleads no contest to cts 1 & 3. 14CF55 - Court reviews repeater penalites. Def understands. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas. 14CF55 - finds guilty of ct 1, ct 2 dismissed and read in. 14CF132 - dismissed and read in. 14CF135 - ct 1  finds guilty, ct 2 dismissed and read in, ct 3 finds guilty. 14CF141 ct 1 finds guilty, ct 2 finds guilty. State recommends plea agreement. Statement by Atty Laufenberg. Nothing by Defendant. Court accepts agreement. Def advised of firearms and voting rights. DNA sample and surcharge on each case appropritate. 14CF55 ct 1 sentence withheld, 1 yr probation, costs. 14CF135, ct 1 withheld sentence, 18 months probation, costs, 27 days credit. Ct 3 - sentence withheld, 18 months probation, 27 days credit. 14CF141 ct 1 - 15 days jail, consecutive to all other sentences, credit for 12 days, completed, costs, pp. ct 2 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, costs. Postconviction rights. All costs include DNA surcharge.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Defendant Larry M Urick in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CF163, 14CF55,  14CF132, 14CF135, 14CF141 @ 11:09 a.m. All cases except 13CF163 scheduled for preliminary hearing. Atty Laufenberg advises Def waives preliminary hrgs. Court reviews prelim rights, finds Def understands and waivers freely made. Probable cause found in all cases. Informations filed. Bonds remain. 13CF163 - motion to revoke to track with arraignments.  Arraignment scheduled for December 17, 2014 at 09:45 am.

Defendant Larry M Urick in court via video with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg in person.  Defendant Larry M Urick in custody.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CF163, 14CF55, 14CF132, 14CF135, and 14CF141 @ 12:11 p.m. Statement by Atty Laufenberg. All to be set for prelim hrg and any motions. Bond remains.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 24, 2014 at 10:45 am.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Larry M Urick in court via video with attorney Jessica L Schuster.  Defendant Larry M Urick in custody.  Ralph M Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   New complaint.  Waive time limits for preliminary.  State request $2500.00 cash to cover all files.  No objections.  Warrants vacated on all files.  13CF163, 14CF55, 14CF132 and 14CF135   Bond set by Court  Status conference scheduled for July 28, 2014 at 03:30 pm.

Attorney Alec Nocco in court.  Ralph M Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CF163, 14CF55, 14CF132 and 14CF135 @ 3:15 p.m. Def called COC and advised would not be appearing. Def spoke to Atty Nocco.  State requests body only warrant on all files. Atty Nocco moves to withdraw. Has advised Def to contact public defender's office. Atty Nocco will file motion.
